Voidface iOS app — scaffold placeholder.

The iOS app runs the trained generator on the Apple Neural Engine
via the CoreML .mlpackage produced by `voidface export --coreml`.
Files never leave the device. The killer feature is a share-sheet
extension that intercepts photos on their way to Instagram / TikTok /
Messages and hands back the protected version.

This directory is intentionally empty until 0.3.0. See
`../../Documentation/deployment/ios.md` for the intended shape:

  * SwiftUI shell (App/)
  * VoidfaceRunner.swift wrapping MLModel
  * ProtectView / BatchView / VideoView
  * ShareExtension target
  * Voidface.mlpackage bundled in the app

0.3.0 gates on:
  * 0.1.0 core (shipped).
  * 0.2.0 trained checkpoint (R5.5).
  * Apple Developer account for signing.
